{
  "abstract" : [
    {
      "text" : "Tutorial for building a simple program for your host OS with Embedded Swift",
      "type" : "text"
    }
  ],
  "hierarchy" : {
    "paths" : [
      [
        "doc:\/\/EmbeddedSwift\/documentation\/EmbeddedSwift"
      ]
    ]
  },
  "identifier" : {
    "interfaceLanguage" : "swift",
    "url" : "doc:\/\/EmbeddedSwift\/documentation\/EmbeddedSwift\/macOSGuide"
  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Try out Embedded Swift on macOS"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "While desktop operating systems like macOS and Linux are not the typical targets for Embedded Swift, you ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "absolutely can",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "strong"
            },
            {
              "text" : " build code for them using the Embedded Swift mode. This is useful for experimentation, trying out Embedded Swift, or to be able to iterate fast on an idea for some code that doesn’t really need the physical device to work.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The simplest program in Embedded Swift can just be a regular “Hello, World”:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\/\/ HelloEmbedded.swift",
            "print(\"Hello, Embedded Swift 😊\")"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "And building it into an executable can be done by calling the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "swiftc",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " compiler directly, but we’ll want to add flags to enable Embedded Swift, and also Whole Module Optimization.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swiftc HelloEmbedded.swift -o HelloEmbedded -enable-experimental-feature Embedded -wmo"
          ],
          "syntax" : "shell",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This will produce a regular executable binary, and we can execute it right away:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ .\/HelloEmbedded",
            "Hello, Embedded Swift 😊"
          ],
          "syntax" : "shell",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Hooray! Our first ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "host-side",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " Embedded Swift program is working!",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Details",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Details",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Looking closer, this binary ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "does not actually depend on the Swift runtime in the OS",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " (all Embedded Swift binaries carry their runtime+stdlib dependencies within), but it is still a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "dynamically-linked executable",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", so it’s not fully standalone in the embedded sense:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ otool -L HelloEmbedded",
            "HelloEmbedded:",
            "        \/usr\/lib\/libSystem.B.dylib (compatibility version 1.0.0, current version 1000.0.0)"
          ],
          "syntax" : "shell",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "However, the singular object file that was used to build this executable was produced by the compiler in the same fashion that a real embedded build would. If we ask the compiler and linker to minimize the size of the outputs and to remove any unused code, we can observe that the binary has no dependencies other than ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "putchar",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " from ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "libSystem",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and that the machine code section is very small (176 bytes in the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "__text",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " section):",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swiftc HelloEmbedded.swift -o HelloEmbedded -enable-experimental-feature Embedded -wmo -Osize -Xlinker -dead_strip",
            "",
            "$ nm -um HelloEmbedded",
            "                 (undefined) external _putchar (from libSystem)",
            "",
            "$ size -m HelloEmbedded",
            "Segment __TEXT: 16384",
            "        Section __text: 176",
            "..."
          ],
          "syntax" : "shell",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In contrast, if compiled without the Embedded Swift flags, we can see the dependencies on the Swift runtime in the OS:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swiftc HelloEmbedded.swift -o HelloEmbedded",
            "",
            "$ otool -L HelloEmbedded",
            "HelloEmbedded:",
            "        \/usr\/lib\/libSystem.B.dylib (compatibility version 1.0.0, current version 1000.0.0)",
            "        \/usr\/lib\/swift\/libswiftCore.dylib (compatibility version 1.0.0, current version 0.0.0)",
            "        \/usr\/lib\/swift\/libswiftSwiftOnoneSupport.dylib (compatibility version 1.0.0, current version 0.0.0)"
          ],
          "syntax" : "shell",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Where-to-go-next",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Where to go next",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The ",
                      "type" : "text"
